Life can get crazy at times.
I always feared the ‚Äúunknown‚Äù and had the fear that someone would figure me out, like I wasn‚Äôt living up to this picture perfect person that everyone perceives me to be. My life on the outside looks like it‚Äôs out of a dream - but I have fears, anxiety, stress, self-doubt, just like anyone else. Slowly I‚Äòm learning to block out the ‚Äúnoise‚Äù by focusing on everything I DO have. Focusing on gratitude has calmed my mind in a way nothing else really could. I have my eyes to see the world clearly, my voice to speak my truth, my mind to think and create visions and ideas for myself, I have my family and friends, who I love more than anything. There is just so much to be grateful for, so when I focus on those things and start my day with that, everything just feels quieter and more at peace. The peace inspires me to move forward, even though not every day is perfect, being grateful is a huge step in the right direction.

The happiness you feel is in direct proportion to the love you are able to give. Happiness does not come from money, a job you want, a car you want, a relationship you want, or anything else external that you desire. I‚Äôve been to some of the most amazing places in the world, had a great relationship, made money, reached all of my ‚Äúgoals‚Äù and I still was not happy until I realized this truth. Happiness comes solely and purely from within and radiates outwards! When you send love out into the world, you will feel happy. When you think beautiful thoughts and share them with others, you will feel happy. When you help someone in need, you will feel happy. It sounds so simple because it really is. Playing games is what I thought I always had to do when meeting someone new, because I was afraid that my vulnerability would somehow make them perceive me as ‚Äúweak‚Äù or ‚Äúfragile‚Äù. For most of my life, I felt like I had to put up this giant wall and maintain a tough exterior out to the world because often when I‚Äôd let it down, I would ultimately get hurt. It always felt easier to be on guard for me with someone I really cared about.
-
As I get older, I‚Äôm learning to accept that I‚Äôm a very emotional person and this is my biggest strength. I have a lot of feeling and I absorb the energy and emotions of other people around me, which is overwhelming at times but also what fulfills me the most. I love giving advice, listening to people, and trying to help them whenever I can. It took me until last year to understand that it‚Äôs powerful to carry on the feelings and emotions of others and to help guide them onto a new path.
-
I‚Äôm still in the process of learning to create healthy boundaries for myself when it comes to loving other people. When I fall in love, I fall hard and I want to heal and provide - but I also know I have to heal and provide for myself. Self-acceptance and self-love ultimately attracts the perfect people and situations to come into your life - so why not always be that way? ‚ù§Ô∏è

Some tips to help you keep on track this week mentally:
‚Ä¢ Remember everything is temporary, including how you feel. Your emotions can be powerful and it can feel like they‚Äôre taking over sometimes, so remind yourself to take a step back and look at the bigger picture.
-
‚Ä¢ Life is short, release the tension and the negative energy surrounding your current situations. You have a brand new day to make new experiences, create positive moments and fulfill yourself in new ways. Don‚Äôt get caught up in the small stuff.
-
- Exercise and incorporate new routines into your day. If I‚Äôm super stressed or sad, I‚Äôll go to the gym to clear my thoughts and my head. My life might seem picture perfect but I have bad days just like anyone else. Working out and eating healthier has helped me physically and mentally feel more productive and aligned with my bigger purpose and my goals.
-
‚Ä¢ Reach out to friends, family, or anyone that you can confide in if you‚Äôre going through something. It‚Äôs important to express yourself and talk it out. The people who love you will be rooting for you even if you‚Äôre going through a hard time, and it can be inspiring to remember that you‚Äôre loved and you have a support team!
-
‚Ä¢Write down your biggest goals for the week and take your time working towards them. Patience and consistency. Don‚Äôt rush the process, enjoy it and remember that the best things take time! Don‚Äôt put unnecessary pressure on yourself. As long as you set the goal and put in effort, eventually you will get there. ‚ù§Ô∏è
